}
  MOVE [/Q] [Dn:][path1>]pattern
            [Dn:][path2]

This command allows you to move files
or subdirectories into another
directory on the same disk. Unlike
COPY, MOVE only changes directory
entries, which is much faster than
copying the entire file. It also
requires no extra free sectors, since
no additional data is created.

Option /Q (quiet) suppresses messages
for each file or directory.

Files and directories can only be
moved within the same disk drive.
